text.tspan: Weekly confirmed cases of influenza B Yamagata, sentinel surveillance
Sentinel surveillance consists of data routinely collected from sites representative of the country's population.
Only a fraction of potential cases of influenza are tested by labs to confirm whether they have influenza and to
identify their strain. The level of testing may vary between countries and over time.
Data source: FluNet by the World Health Organization (2023)
Note: This shows the number of cases that were confirmed to be of the Yamagata lineage of influenza B virus.
